{{Infobox journal | title = Notices of the American Mathematical Society | cover = NAMS.jpg | caption= March 2005 issue | abbreviation=Notices Am. Math. Soc. | nlm=Not Am Math Soc | mathscinet=Notices Amer. Math. Soc. | editor = [[Frank Morgan (mathematician)|Frank Morgan]] | discipline= [[Mathematics]] | language = [[English language|English]] | publisher = [[American Mathematical Society]] | history = 1953–present | country = United States | frequency = Monthly, except combined June/July issue | website = http://www.ams.org/notices/ | link1 = | link1-name = | ISSN = 0002-9920 | eISSN= 1088-9477 }} '''''Notices of the American Mathematical Society''''' is the membership [[Academic journal|journal]] of the [[American Mathematical Society]] (AMS), published monthly except for the combined June/July issue. The first volume appeared in 1953. Each issue of the magazine since January 1995 is available in its entirety on the journal web site. Articles are peer-reviewed by an editorial board of mathematical experts. Since 2016, the [[editor-in-chief]] is [[Frank Morgan (mathematician)|Frank Morgan]]. The cover regularly features [[mathematical visualization]]s.
The ''Notices'' is the world's most widely read mathematical journal.<ref>[http://www.ams.org/notices/about.html About ''Notices of the AMS'']</ref> As the membership journal of the American Mathematical Society, the ''Notices'' is sent to the approximately 30,000 AMS members worldwide, one-third of whom reside outside the United States. By publishing high-level exposition, the ''Notices'' provides opportunities for mathematicians to find out what is going on in the field. Each issue contains one or two such expository articles that describe current developments in mathematical research, written by professional mathematicians. The ''Notices'' also carries articles on the history of mathematics, mathematics education, and professional issues facing mathematicians, as well as reviews of books and other works.
