{{Infobox scientist |name = Semën Kutateladze |image = Kutateladze Semen.jpg | caption = Semën Kutateladze |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1945|10|02}} |birth_place = [[Leningrad]], [[USSR]] |nationality = |death_date = |death_place = |field = [[Mathematics]] |work_institution = [[Sobolev Institute of Mathematics]], [[Novosibirsk State University]] |alma_mater = [[Novosibirsk State University]] |doctoral_advisor = G.Sh. Rubinstein |doctoral_students = |known_for = |prizes = | signature = |footnotes = }}
'''Semën Samsonovich Kutateladze''' (born October 2, 1945 in [[Leningrad]], now [[St. Petersburg]]) is a [[mathematics|mathematician]]. He is known for contributions to [[functional analysis]] and its applications to [[vector lattice]]s and [[mathematical optimization|optimization]]. <ref>{{cite journal|mr=1480167|last1=[[Aleksandr Danilovich Aleksandrov|Aleksandrov]]|first1=A. D.|last2=[[Olga Ladyzhenskaya|Ladyzhenskaya]]|first2=O. A.|last3=[[ Yurii Reshetnyak| Reshetnyak]]|first3=Yu. G.|title=Semën Samsonovich Kutateladze (on his 50th birthday)|journal=Russian Math. Surveys|volume=52|issue=2|year=1997|pages=447&ndash;450|url=http://www.turpion.org/php/paper.phtml?journal_id=rm&paper_id=1807}}</ref> <ref>{{cite journal|mr=2178006 | last1=Gutman|first1=A. E.|last2=Kusraev|first2=A. G.|last3=Reshetnyak|first3=Yu. G.|title= On the nth birthday of Semën Samsonovich Kutateladze for n=60|journal= Sib. Èlektron. Mat. Izv.|volume= 2|year=2005|pages= A.12&ndash;A.33|url=http://mi.mathnet.ru/semr48}}</ref> In particular, he has made contributions to the [[differential calculus|calculus]] of [[subdifferential]]s for vector-lattice valued functions, to whose study he introduced methods of [[Boolean-valued model]]s and [[infinitesimal]]s.
He is professor of mathematics at [[Novosibirsk State University]],<ref>[http://www.math.nsc.ru/LBRT/g2/ruswin/ssk/ About Kutateladze in Russian]</ref> where he has continued and enriched the scientific tradition of [[Leonid Kantorovich]]. <ref>{{cite book|first=Lev&nbsp;J.,&nbsp;ed.|last=Leifman|title=Functional analysis, optimization, and mathematical economics: A collection of papers dedicated to the memory of Leonid Vitalʹevich Kantorovich|publisher=The Clarendon Press, Oxford University Press|location=New York|year=1990|pages=xvi+341|isbn=0-19-505729-5|mr=1082562}}</ref> <ref>Kutateladze, S.S., [http://www.jams.or.jp/notice/Notices0701.pdf "The World Line of Kantorovich"], ''Notices of the ISMS'', International Society for Mathematical Sciences, Osaka, Japan, January 2007.</ref> <ref>Kutateladze, S.S., [http://www.math.nsc.ru/LBRT/g2/english/ssk/lvk_phenomenon_e.html "Kantorovich's Phenomenon"], ''Siberian Mathematical Journal '''' (Сибирский мат. журн.), 2007, V. 48, No. 1, 3–4, November 29, 2006.</ref> <ref>Kutateladze, S.S., [http://www.math.nsc.ru/LBRT/g2/english/ssk/lvk100_e.html "Mathematics and Economics of Kantorovich"]</ref> His father was a heat physicist [[Samson Kutateladze]].
